\lim_{T\rightarrow0}(S_{2}-S_{1}) & = & \lim_{T\rightarrow0}\Big(c\ln\Big(\frac{T_{2}}{T_{1}}\Big)+a(V_{2}-V_{1})\Big)\\
 & = & \lim_{T\rightarrow0}\Big(c\ln(1)+a(V_{2}-V_{1})\Big)\\
 & = & a(V_{2}-V_{1})
\end{eqnarray*}

\end_inset

Since this term does not necessarily go to zero as the temperature drops
 the equations are not valid for very low temperatures.
